des:
If you have any question when you use this skill, you can contact us with email : feedback@NOSHADO.NET
Amazon Alexa and the Ispakle RGB products work together to help you control your lights by voice control.

You can simply ask Alexa to turn on, turn off or dim the light. 
You don’t need your app, phone or handling the lights - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo, Echo Dot, Amazon Tap or Echo Show. 

After connecting Alexa to your Isparkle RGB products in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "Isparkle RGB" app in android or ios app market;
(2) You need to have some Isparkle RGB device in hand;
(3). Register your Isparkle account in our "Isparkle RGB" app;
(4). Configure these devices in our “Isparkle RGB" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Isparkle" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Isparkle" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Isparkle", and you'll be navigated to Isparkle login page;
(9). Input your Isparkle account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished. 

You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on light”
“Alexa, turn off light”
“Alexa, set the light to red”
